THE Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC) will hold its Annual General Meeting on December 12, 2019 at Starview Palace Hotel, Gwarimpa Estate in FCT, Abuja. Coming on the heels of hosting the International Olympic Committee President, Dr Thomas Bach for the commissioning of the Association of National Olympic Committee of Africa (ANOCA), secretariat in Abuja,Â  the NOC will discuss amongst other issues the level of preparedness for the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. The AGM will also feature a Patrons forum where the NOC will interact with distinguished Patrons and further highlight their roles and responsibilities. According to the notice of meeting signed by Olabanji Oladapo, Secretary General of NOC, the Patrons Forum is scheduled to take place on Wednesday, December 11, 2019 by 2.00pm at the same venue of the AGM while the Congress comes up on December 12.